    <title>Basic Ice Tea</title>

    <comment></comment>
    <thumbnail>../images/placeholder.png</thumbnail>
    <image></image>
    <category></category>
    <yield></yield>
    <prepTime></prepTime>
    <cookTime></cookTime>
    <part></part>



    <ingredient>4 cups boiling water</ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 teabags</ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 TBsp sugar (optional)</ingredient>
    <ingredient>4 cups cold water</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1/4 lemon juice</ingredient>
    <ingredient>Ice blocks and garnishes</ingredient>

    <step>
In a heatproof jug pour in boiling water and add teabags and sugar. Brew tea for 5 minutes and remove teabags. Pour in cold water, lemon juice and refrigerate until cold. Pour in tall glasses filled with ice and garnish with fresh fruit and/or lemon and mint leaves.
    </step>
</recipe>